               <msContents>
                  <summary>Pasion and Berenike submit a joint will stating that in the event of either's death the survivor maintain full control of all assets and possessions and full authority to divide these among children as survivor sees fit.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Margins: left, 1.3 cm.; 46 2B</note>
                     <note type="general">On the date, see Cockle, W.E.H., Euripides: Hypsipyle, (Rome 1987),196-197 and van Minnen, P., P.Lugd.Bat. XXX, pp. 60f.</note>
                     <note type="lines">23 lines, on recto along the fibers.</note>
                     <note type="paleography">Three hands: 1st (lines 1-7, 8-15), careful hand; 2nd (half of line 7) and 3rd (15-23), more cursive.</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Verso empty.</note>
